        </div>

        <p><strong>Where Writesonic wins:</strong> if you need 80+ short-form copy tools in one tab, or if AI Visibility tracking matters to you, nothing in the price range matches it. <strong>Where theStacc wins:</strong> if your job is shipping SEO content at scale without editing and publishing it personally.</p>

        <h2 id="what-is">What is Writesonic?</h2>
        <p>Writesonic is an AI writing platform founded in 2020 by Samanyou Garg. It started as a short-form copy tool with templates for ads, headlines, and product descriptions. It has since grown into a broad suite covering blog articles, AI chat (Chatsonic), image generation (Photosonic), chatbot building (Botsonic), and AI search visibility tracking.</p>

        <p>The platform now does five major things:</p>

        <ol>
          <li><strong>AI Article Writer</strong> — keyword in, full article draft out (1,500–3,000 words)</li>
          <li><strong>80+ Templates</strong> — ads, emails, product descriptions, headlines, landing pages</li>
          <li><strong>Chatsonic</strong> — ChatGPT-style assistant with web access, voice input, image generation</li>
          <li><strong>AI Visibility</strong> — tracks brand mentions in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Google AI Overviews</li>
          <li><strong>Botsonic + Photosonic</strong> — custom AI chatbots and image generation</li>
        </ol>

        <p>What Writesonic is <em>not</em>: a true auto-publishing platform, a deep SERP analysis tool, or a done-for-you service. It generates content. You edit, optimise, and publish it.</p>

        <div class="callout callout-info">
          <div class="callout-label">ℹ️ Company background</div>
          <p>Writesonic was founded in 2020 in Bengaluru, India by Samanyou Garg. The company has raised over $35M including a Series A led by Insight Partners. The platform serves 5M+ users across solo marketers, agencies, and content teams. The AI Visibility product, launched in 2024, is the company's strongest current bet on GEO becoming mainstream.</p>
        </div>

        <h2 id="features">Writesonic features — the full 2026 walkthrough</h2>

        <h3>1. AI Article Writer</h3>
        <p>The headline content feature. Enter a target keyword, pick a title, generate an outline, and Writesonic produces a full draft. The output is comparable to GPT-4 with a content-marketing prompt. Quality is decent. The article does not score against the top-10 results (Surfer does this better), and you will spend 15–30 minutes editing and reformatting before publishing.</p>

        <h3>2. 80+ Templates</h3>
        <p>The reason most users land on Writesonic. Templates cover Facebook ads, Google ads, Instagram captions, product descriptions, cold emails, SEO meta tags, landing page hero copy, YouTube descriptions, podcast outlines, and many more. Solo marketers love this surface area. Content-focused teams ignore most of it.</p>

        <h3>3. Chatsonic — AI chat with web access</h3>
        <p>Writesonic's ChatGPT competitor. Live web access (Chatsonic browses current pages), voice input, image generation, and persistent memory. Convenient inside the same surface as the templates. Output quality is slightly below GPT-4 and Claude.</p>

        <h3>4. AI Visibility — the standout feature</h3>
        <p>The most interesting product in the suite. Track how often your brand surfaces in ChatGPT, Perplexity, Claude, and Google AI Overviews for relevant queries. Get prompt-level visibility data, competitor share, and trending mentions. Only on the Advanced plan ($499/mo) — but if GEO is a 2026 priority, this is hard to find elsewhere.</p>

        <h3>5. Botsonic + Photosonic</h3>
        <p>Botsonic lets you build a branded support chatbot trained on your docs (no-code). Photosonic generates images from text prompts. Both are competent but not best-in-class — Intercom Fin and Midjourney lead their respective categories.</p>

        <h3>6. WordPress export</h3>
        <p>Export an article directly to WordPress as a draft. It is not scheduled auto-publishing — you still log in, finish formatting, add internal links, set the SEO meta, and hit Publish. Plan on 15–30 minutes per article post-export.</p>

        <h2 id="pricing">Writesonic pricing — what it really costs in 2026</h2>
        <p>Writesonic publishes credit-based pricing. The headline word allowance hides a credit multiplier that determines real output.</p>

